So another thing I want to mention is that I'm using the preview version of RStudio now.

00:16:53.000 --> 00:16:58.000
So it's 0.99.1251.

00:16:58.000 --> 00:17:00.000
So that's the preview version.

00:17:00.000 --> 00:17:06.000
If you don't know where to download the preview version, you can simply Google for RStudio preview version.

00:17:06.000 --> 00:17:14.000
So the reason to use the preview version of RStudio is that with RStudio preview version,

00:17:14.000 --> 00:17:26.000
you will see a build tab here, and there is a menu here listing the possible output formats of your book.

00:17:26.000 --> 00:17:29.000
And the first one is Gitbook.

00:17:29.000 --> 00:17:40.000
So let's just click this build book button to build these RMD files into the Gitbook format.

00:17:40.000 --> 00:17:44.000
So this is the Gitbook format that I just mentioned.

00:17:44.000 --> 00:17:50.000
And let me just walk you through the layout of the Gitbook style.

00:17:50.000 --> 00:17:57.000
So the Gitbook output is essentially some HTML web pages.

00:17:57.000 --> 00:18:04.000
So each chapter will be a single page by default.

00:18:04.000 --> 00:18:11.000
So you can navigate through the book by clicking the navigation button at the bottom.

00:18:11.000 --> 00:18:18.000
The button is at the bottom because my screen is very narrow right now.

00:18:18.000 --> 00:18:28.000
If your screen is wide enough, you can see the navigation button will be on the left and right side.

00:18:28.000 --> 00:18:35.000
So you can navigate to the second chapter or the third chapter.

00:18:35.000 --> 00:18:38.000
So you can navigate through different pages.

00:18:38.000 --> 00:18:46.000
And so on the left side, you can see there's a table of contents showing the chapter titles.

00:18:46.000 --> 00:18:50.000
And of course, you can collapse the sidebar.

00:18:50.000 --> 00:18:58.000
So especially when your screen is too narrow, you may want to just hide the table of contents on the left.

