So one thing that I mentioned earlier is that you are able to number your figures and tables.

00:31:14.000 --> 00:31:22.000
And the way to do that is that the code chunks will have some chunk labels.

00:31:22.000 --> 00:31:27.000
For example, I have a nice fig for this code chunk.

00:31:27.000 --> 00:31:41.000
And then if you are using Bookdown, you will be able to refer to this figure using the syntax backslash at ref in parentheses.

00:31:41.000 --> 00:31:50.000
Then the figure label, which is fig colon followed by the chunk label.

00:31:51.000 --> 00:31:58.000
So that's how you can refer the figures.

00:31:58.000 --> 00:32:01.000
And for tables, it's the same.

00:32:01.000 --> 00:32:12.000
So see, you have this in the IMD source document, and you have the actual figure number in the output.

00:32:12.000 --> 00:32:17.000
And your figure is numbered here, figure 2.1.

00:32:21.000 --> 00:32:26.000
And there are many other features.

00:32:26.000 --> 00:32:36.000
And you can know more about these features from the Bookdown documentation, which you can find on bookdown.org.

